---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Arclet Copier" lang="en">
  <Header lang="en" />

  <main class="pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-soft-lg p-8 md:p-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-serif font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <p class="text-secondary-600 mb-8">Last updated: December 3, 2025</p>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-4">
              Your Privacy Matters
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 mb-4">
              We don't collect your data. Period.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 mb-4">
              No personal info. No browsing history. No tracking what you copy. Nothing gets sent anywhere.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary-700">
              Your data stays yours. Always.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-4">What Stays on Your Device</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 mb-4">
              Some things live on your computer to make Arclet Copier work the way you want:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-secondary-700 space-y-2">
              <li>Your settings and preferences</li>
              <li>Your custom templates and rules</li>
              <li>Your copy history—stored locally, never uploaded</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 mt-4">
              This stays on your device. We don't see it. No one else does either.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-4">Why We Need Permissions</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 mb-4">
              The browser asks for permissions. Here's why we need them:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-secondary-700 space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong>activeTab</strong>—To copy URLs from the page you're on
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>tabs</strong>—To handle multiple tabs in batch operations
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>storage</strong>—To remember your settings
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>notifications</strong>—To let you know when copying is done
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>offscreen</strong>—To generate QR codes in the background
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>clipboardWrite</strong>—To put clean URLs in your clipboard
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>contextMenus</strong>—To add right-click menu options
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 mt-4">
              Nothing more, nothing less. We only use what's needed.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-4">Short Link Services</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700">
              When you generate short links, your URL gets sent to the service you choose—is.gd or TinyURL. They have their own privacy policies.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 mt-4">
              We don't control what they do. Choose what you trust.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-4">Analytics</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700">
              We may use self-hosted Umami to track usage patterns, bugs, and performance. This helps us make things better.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 mt-4">
              No personal data. No tracking across sites. Just basic stats to improve the tool.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-4">Your Data is Safe</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700">
              Can't breach what we don't have. Your data never leaves your device, so there's nothing to leak.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 mt-4">
              Privacy by design. Security by default.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-4">If This Changes</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700">
              We'll update this page when things change. We won't notify you separately—check back here if you're curious.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 mt-4">
              We respect your time. We won't change things lightly.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-secondary-900 mb-4">Questions?</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 mb-4">
              Reach out via email or Discord. We're here to help.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary-700">
              Email:
              <a
                href="mailto:hi@coryso.com"
                class="text-primary-600 underline hover:text-primary-700"
              >
                hi@coryso.com
              </a>
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 mt-2">
              Discord:
              <a
                href="https://discord.gg/NpRnQ5zp5q"
                class="text-primary-600 underline hover:text-primary-700"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                Join our community
              </a>
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer lang="en" />
</Layout>
